==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''ortgeard'', a compound of ''ort'', either from ''wyrt'', ''wort'' (plant) or from Latin [[hortus]] and ''geard'', see [[yard]]
===Noun===
'''orchard'''

# a [[garden]] or an area of land to the cultivation of fruit or nut trees; or the trees themselves cultivated in such an area
